    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows two disks. Disk A has radius r sub 0. Disk B has radius 2 r sub 0. Strings are wrapped around the edge of each disk and the strings are pulled with equal forces of magnitude F toward the right so that each disk rotates clockwise.\" src=\"/images/9c9251b9d435d8c17e3c401b90de3675.svg\"></div></div></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Disks <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>A</mtext></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>B</mtext></math></span></span> are initially at rest. Strings with negligible mass are wrapped around the edge of each disk and the strings are pulled with equal forces of magnitude <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F\"><math alttext=\"F\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>F</mi></math></span></span>, as shown. The disks are free to rotate about their centers with negligible friction. Disk <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>A</mtext></math></span></span> has radius <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"r sub 0\"><math alttext=\"r sub 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></span></span> and rotational inertia <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"I sub 0\"><math alttext=\"I sub 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>I</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></span></span>. Disk <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>B</mtext></math></span></span> has radius <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2 r sub 0\"><math alt